The paper deals with minimum cut problems that have applications in network security, specifically in the context of DDoS attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves algorithmic and computational aspects, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper mentions planar graphs, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses information theory, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.IT (Information Theory).
